fields.value: Handbook of International Data on Women

dsDescriptionValue.value:
These data resulted from a project designed to bring together in one source every category of data collected about women around the world. Although not complete, a great volume of data was collected and valuable indicators were created to help in the analysis of the data.

"For each indicator, there are two indexes: (1) index of femaleness and (2) distribution index. For example, the index of femaleness of mining and quarrying measures the proportion of women who are employed in the tota l industrial labor force that engages in mining and manufacturing. The second index measures the proportion of persons in one particular category to all persons in a group of related categories. Indicators are presented in the following categories: general economic activity; economic activity by status; economic activity by industry; economic activity by occupation; literacy and education; migration; marital status; life, death, and reproduction; and political and civic participation."
